setwd('/Users/song/Desktop/Datamining/session 4')
indian = read.csv('PimaIndians.csv')
head(indian)
set.seed(5)
s = sample(nrow(indian),floor(nrow(indian)*0.6))
train = indian[s,]
eval = indian[-s,]
head(train)
res=glm(Class~.,data=train)
summary(res)

eval$Prediction=predict(res,eval,type="response")
head(eval)
hist(eval$Prediction)

mean(eval$Prediction)
[1] 0.3319249
falsePositive = eval[eval$Prediction >= 0.5 & eval$Class==0,]
falseNegative = eval[eval$Prediction < 0.5 & eval$Class==1,]
error = (nrow(falseNegative) + nrow(falsePositive))/nrow(eval)
error
[1] 0.1883117
options(scipen = 999)
xaxis = dim(nrow(eval)) # amount of eval-set
cumMean = dim(nrow(eval))
cumLift = dim(nrow(eval))
meanResponse = mean(eval$Class)
xaxis[1] = 1
cumMean[1] = meanResponse
eval[1:3,]
evalOrdered = eval[order(eval$Prediction, decreasing = TRUE),]
evalOrdered[1:3,]
cumLift[1] = evalOrdered$Class[1]
for(i in 2:nrow(eval)){
  xaxis[i] = i
  cumMean[i] = cumMean[i-1] + meanResponse
  cumLift[i] = cumLift[i-1] + evalOrdered$Class[i]
}
plot(cumLift~xaxis)
points(cumLift~xaxis)

library(ROCR)
pred = prediction(eval$Prediction, eval$Class)
roc = performance(pred,"sens","fpr")
plot(roc)
